  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with a complex legal framework. Here's an overview of key aspects:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group international cooperation\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (UK)\n- Various national anti-money laundering (AML) statutes\n\n3. Regulatory Compliance Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Risk assessment protocols\n\n4. Criminalization Elements\n- Concealing illegal financial proceeds\n- Disguising source of funds\n- Transferring criminal assets\n- Intentional financial obfuscation\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- International law enforcement cooperation\n\n6. Reporting Obligations\n- Financial institutions must report suspicious activities\n- Threshold transaction reporting\n- Cross-border financial movement tracking\n\nThis framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across jurisdictions.",
